WEBVTT

1
00:01:16.410 --> 00:01:19.378
(All characters. locations. organizations. religions. )

2
00:01:19.379 --> 00:01:22.050
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

3
00:01:47.609 --> 00:01:48.710
Tak Dong Kyung.

4
00:01:50.479 --> 00:01:52.079
How do you know my name?

5
00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:53.479
Who are you?

6
00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:55.589
Then. who are you?

7
00:02:02.589 --> 00:02:03.898
It's cold tonight.

8
00:02:03.899 --> 00:02:06.699
Why did she leave? She could catch a cold. Goodness.

9
00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:07.830
Tak Dong Kyung.

10
00:02:09.529 --> 00:02:11.398
First floor. The doors are closing.

11
00:02:11.399 --> 00:02:12.669
Going down.

12
00:02:16.309 --> 00:02:18.579
- What was that about? - My aunt.

13
00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:20.248
If she sees us. things will get complicated.

14
00:02:20.249 --> 00:02:22.079
If we want to talk. I can't let her catch us.

15
00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:23.210
Talk about what?

16
00:02:24.680 --> 00:02:26.649
Aren't you here because you needed to talk to me?

17
00:02:27.119 --> 00:02:28.418
I doubt that you came back because you missed me...

18
00:02:28.419 --> 00:02:29.720
since we just saw each other.

19
00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:34.589
Why did you ask me who I was?

20
00:02:34.960 --> 00:02:36.489
You even know my name.

21
00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:37.699
Then. what about your question?

22
00:02:38.199 --> 00:02:41.399
I explained to you who I am and what I do.

23
00:02:44.139 --> 00:02:45.270
I don't know.

24
00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:48.070
Something feels weird.

25
00:02:51.039 --> 00:02:52.309
Second basement floor.

26
00:02:54.710 --> 00:02:56.809
- Where are we going? - To the parking lot.

27
00:02:57.119 --> 00:02:58.550
This will be a long conversation.

28
00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:07.759
(Episode 13)

29
00:03:17.839 --> 00:03:19.040
I need to ask you something.

30
00:03:21.270 --> 00:03:23.010
It's cold out here. Let's talk inside.

31
00:03:24.010 --> 00:03:25.180
I can't do that inside.

32
00:03:28.110 --> 00:03:29.309
I'll lose there...

33
00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:31.779
because it's your turf.

34
00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:34.550
- Then. this place works for you? - No.

35
00:03:36.119 --> 00:03:37.659
There isn't such a place.

36
00:03:39.819 --> 00:03:40.890
I picked this place...

37
00:03:42.159 --> 00:03:44.029
because it'd be easier to run away if I wanted.

38
00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.670
Let's stop skirting around it now.

39
00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:02.050
- Joo Ik. - Yes.

40
00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:04.719
Did you kiss her?

41
00:04:06.649 --> 00:04:07.819
Did you...

42
00:04:10.760 --> 00:04:12.020
kiss her 10 years ago?

43
00:04:13.790 --> 00:04:15.390
- Yes. - Why?

44
00:04:15.629 --> 00:04:16.890
To get her out of there.

45
00:04:17.960 --> 00:04:19.499
So you two wouldn't get back together.

46
00:04:22.300 --> 00:04:23.369
Why?

47
00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:28.369
She cried there every single day.

48
00:04:29.569 --> 00:04:31.409
If I didn't make her leave that day.

49
00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:35.210
she would have cried. sitting on that step for days and months.

50
00:04:36.809 --> 00:04:38.020
I didn't want her...

51
00:04:38.680 --> 00:04:40.819
to come back again. sit there. and cry.

52
00:04:43.619 --> 00:04:45.890
- That's why I did it. - Did you think about me?

53
00:04:48.159 --> 00:04:49.589
- Did you? - I did.

54
00:04:50.499 --> 00:04:51.760
All the more reason why I did it.

55
00:04:53.099 --> 00:04:55.629
You knew that she was waiting for you.

56
00:04:56.399 --> 00:04:58.269
You knew. but you never went out to see her...

57
00:04:58.270 --> 00:04:59.469
because you were embarrassed.

58
00:05:00.740 --> 00:05:02.338
You left Korea as if you were never going to come back.

59
00:05:02.339 --> 00:05:04.409
but you came back only after a few months because it was tough.

60
00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:06.409
You didn't want her to find out.

61
00:05:11.279 --> 00:05:12.550
Say something.

62
00:05:13.279 --> 00:05:15.189
Curse me out if you want. I'll handle it.

63
00:05:15.790 --> 00:05:16.920
I won't run away.

64
00:05:17.659 --> 00:05:19.260
Why are you brutally honest?

65
00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:21.360
You could have avoided answering it.

66
00:05:22.259 --> 00:05:23.959
apologized. and moved on.

67
00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:27.400
You have a way with words too.

68
00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:30.540
Why are you brutally honest with me?

69
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:32.740
Because I like you.

70
00:05:37.939 --> 00:05:38.980
You are...

71
00:05:39.709 --> 00:05:41.550
one of a few people I actually like.

72
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:44.650
I don't want to be a coward in front of you.

73
00:05:47.319 --> 00:05:48.819
I've hidden it for too long.

74
00:05:50.019 --> 00:05:51.160
And all these years.

75
00:05:54.389 --> 00:05:56.129
it had been bothering me too.

76
00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:04.170
This is so annoying.

77
00:06:09.910 --> 00:06:12.740
You still make me feel worthless even in this moment.

78
00:06:14.079 --> 00:06:15.650
You're so annoying.

79
00:06:18.379 --> 00:06:19.550
Where are you going?

80
00:06:20.550 --> 00:06:22.389
- To the cafe. - Why?

81
00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:25.389
I don't think I can sleep in the same house with you tonight.

82
00:06:32.730 --> 00:06:34.400
I regret every moment of it.

83
00:06:36.170 --> 00:06:39.100
Running away. taking too long.

84
00:06:40.639 --> 00:06:41.809
and asking you.

85
00:06:44.079 --> 00:06:45.110
Everything.

86
00:07:02.829 --> 00:07:04.259
I was crying.

87
00:07:06.499 --> 00:07:08.498
I looked in the mirror after I came back.

88
00:07:08.499 --> 00:07:09.829
And I was crying.

89
00:07:10.939 --> 00:07:12.699
But I didn't even know I was crying.

90
00:07:13.040 --> 00:07:16.740
When I looked in the mirror. I was crying.

91
00:07:20.850 --> 00:07:22.550
Why was I crying?

92
00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:32.819
Get in.

93
00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:36.029
Where are we going?

94
00:07:36.030 --> 00:07:37.629
You'll be safe. Get in.

95
00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:45.540
Have you seen...

96
00:07:46.939 --> 00:07:49.568
a girl who's about this tall and has hair coming up to here?

97
00:07:49.569 --> 00:07:50.910
Have you?

98
00:07:53.009 --> 00:07:55.349
A girl who's about this tall and has hair coming up to here?

99
00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:56.409
That description fits so many girls.

100
00:07:56.410 --> 00:07:58.550
Have you met someone like her at the hospital?

101
00:07:59.949 --> 00:08:02.519
- Are you talking about her? - Have you met her?

102
00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:04.559
What did she do to you?

103
00:08:04.860 --> 00:08:06.519
She didn't do anything. I did something for her.

104
00:08:06.819 --> 00:08:08.689
I opened a bottle for her.

105
00:08:09.530 --> 00:08:10.559
What else?

106
00:08:11.329 --> 00:08:12.329
What else?

107
00:08:15.100 --> 00:08:17.698
After that. she thanked me and told me to go to the rooftop.

108
00:08:17.699 --> 00:08:18.939
She said the view there was nice.

109
00:08:20.170 --> 00:08:22.139
- Anything else other than that? - No.

110
00:08:23.809 --> 00:08:26.410
Think again. I'm sure she did something to you.

111
00:08:27.480 --> 00:08:28.549
What did she do?

112
00:08:28.550 --> 00:08:30.550
That's what I don't know. So think again.

113
00:08:38.819 --> 00:08:39.889
I don't know.

114
00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:43.159
What do you know then?

115
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:45.530
What does she have to do with us?

116
00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:46.900
Does she know me?

117
00:08:47.400 --> 00:08:49.328
I can't remember her either?

118
00:08:49.329 --> 00:08:51.169
Perhaps. your brain has just gone bad. not sick.

119
00:08:51.170 --> 00:08:52.600
No need to talk about yourself now.

120
00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:56.569
Right. I'm not exactly kind.

121
00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:01.249
All good. right? It's my turn now.

122
00:09:03.809 --> 00:09:05.019
You weren't crying?

123
00:09:08.689 --> 00:09:09.949
Why won't you answer my question?

124
00:09:10.150 --> 00:09:12.759
I asked if you weren't crying. Was I the only one who cried?

125
00:09:16.559 --> 00:09:18.059
I'm not done with my questions yet.

126
00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:21.400
Who were you calling earlier?

127
00:09:21.800 --> 00:09:24.300
Exactly. That's really weird.

128
00:09:24.740 --> 00:09:26.040
I was crying.

129
00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:28.240
But I couldn't get that thought out of my head.

130
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:31.840
"I must call you."

131
00:09:33.809 --> 00:09:35.910
- "You"? - But...

132
00:09:36.309 --> 00:09:38.680
I don't know who that person is.

133
00:09:39.349 --> 00:09:41.419
That person's number is saved on my cell phone.

134
00:09:41.420 --> 00:09:42.989
But I have no idea who it is.

135
00:09:46.319 --> 00:09:47.459
Call that number again.

136
00:09:52.959 --> 00:09:56.098
(Call log)

137
00:09:56.099 --> 00:09:57.599
(Human)

138
00:10:05.180 --> 00:10:08.250
Whoever it is isn't picking up. Whose number is this?

139
00:10:10.880 --> 00:10:13.849
"Human". Who's "Human"?

140
00:10:14.920 --> 00:10:17.719
Who knows? At least I know it's not me.

141
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:19.260
I should go now.

142
00:10:19.959 --> 00:10:20.959
What about me?

143
00:10:21.729 --> 00:10:22.729
What?

144
00:10:22.959 --> 00:10:24.399
Aren't you going to drive me back?

145
00:10:24.400 --> 00:10:25.499
It's nearby.

146
00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:27.000
Walk back. It's only five minutes by foot.

147
00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:33.099
Gosh. if he were human I would've taught him a lesson.

148
00:10:38.510 --> 00:10:40.109
Who could it be?

149
00:10:41.079 --> 00:10:42.079
"Human".

150
00:10:49.050 --> 00:10:50.449
Why do you fall so easily?

151
00:10:50.719 --> 00:10:52.559
Watch where you're going.

152
00:10:52.890 --> 00:10:53.919
I thought you were leaving.

153
00:10:53.920 --> 00:10:55.189
Yes. I was on my way.

154
00:10:58.059 --> 00:11:00.969
My gosh. Seriously.

155
00:11:01.630 --> 00:11:03.329
He must be mad in the head.

156
00:11:28.059 --> 00:11:29.760
(Missed call: Dong Kyung)

157
00:12:27.489 --> 00:12:30.448
(Business proposal)

158
00:12:30.449 --> 00:12:33.260
(Sales and Marketing Plan)

159
00:12:35.160 --> 00:12:37.660
(The Story of Genius Minds. Welcome to Genius)

160
00:12:39.430 --> 00:12:43.129
(Friday. Saturday. Sunday)

161
00:12:43.130 --> 00:12:45.799
(My love confession is either always too early or too late.)

162
00:12:45.800 --> 00:12:47.769
(My love confession...)

163
00:12:47.770 --> 00:12:51.679
(is either always too early or too late.)

164
00:12:51.680 --> 00:12:53.510
(From "The Romantic Egoists")

165
00:13:01.150 --> 00:13:02.390
My gosh. he startled me.

166
00:13:05.620 --> 00:13:08.160
Mr. Lee. Mr. Lee!

167
00:13:11.160 --> 00:13:13.300
Oh. hey. Gosh.

168
00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:14.969
You're here.

169
00:13:15.130 --> 00:13:16.468
Did you sleep here?

170
00:13:16.469 --> 00:13:18.370
- Yes. - Why?

171
00:13:19.199 --> 00:13:20.699
Did you fight with your friend?

172
00:13:22.809 --> 00:13:23.809
No.

173
00:13:24.839 --> 00:13:25.880
Then what?

174
00:13:26.709 --> 00:13:27.809
We're still fighting.

175
00:13:29.849 --> 00:13:32.150
They're always fighting. It's like they're a married couple.

176
00:13:36.819 --> 00:13:39.160
Here's the business proposal you asked for. Take a look.

177
00:13:46.059 --> 00:13:48.068
Did you fight with Hyun Kyu?

178
00:13:48.069 --> 00:13:51.040
What are you talking about? Does it look like I fought with him?

179
00:13:51.569 --> 00:13:53.540
I guess you guys didn't have a fistfight yet.

180
00:13:53.939 --> 00:13:56.308
I'm not going to fight him. Plus. I'd win anyway.

181
00:13:56.309 --> 00:13:59.339
Is that so? You think you'll win? Are you sure about that?

182
00:14:00.579 --> 00:14:01.650
So you lost.

183
00:14:02.079 --> 00:14:04.819
- We haven't fought yet. - Then go ahead and fight.

184
00:14:05.150 --> 00:14:07.620
You won't know who will win until you actually fight him.

185
00:14:07.650 --> 00:14:10.250
Do you want me to go around fighting people?

186
00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:13.319
Do you know why I adore Hyun Kyu so much?

187
00:14:13.790 --> 00:14:16.359
Maybe it's because he grew up as an athlete.

188
00:14:16.430 --> 00:14:20.229
but behind that smile of his. I can tell he's very competitive.

189
00:14:20.699 --> 00:14:22.370
I really like that about him.

190
00:14:23.870 --> 00:14:25.269
Whatever.

191
00:14:25.270 --> 00:14:26.770
You're nothing like him.

192
00:14:27.270 --> 00:14:28.669
When he's in for a competition.

193
00:14:28.670 --> 00:14:31.309
he does everything he can to win. but look at you.

194
00:14:31.609 --> 00:14:33.640
You always just yield as if it doesn't even matter.

195
00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:36.409
I bet he's pretty irritated though.

196
00:14:36.410 --> 00:14:38.819
You always let him win without even putting up a fight.

197
00:14:43.120 --> 00:14:44.589
Things are a bit different this time.

198
00:14:45.589 --> 00:14:46.620
How so?

199
00:14:47.290 --> 00:14:48.790
We're not fighting.

200
00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:50.890
But I need to take something from him.

201
00:14:51.930 --> 00:14:52.930
Really?

202
00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:56.900
Then I guess you'll win this time.

203
00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:03.438
I've never seen you fail to get what you want.

204
00:15:03.439 --> 00:15:04.640
And the same goes with this.

205
00:15:05.380 --> 00:15:06.540
I'm looking forward to it.

206
00:15:07.809 --> 00:15:09.879
If you lose but refuse to admit to it.

207
00:15:09.880 --> 00:15:11.379
that would make you a bad mentor.

208
00:15:11.380 --> 00:15:13.519
But if he loses and doesn't back off.

209
00:15:13.520 --> 00:15:14.890
that would mean you didn't teach him well.

210
00:15:18.620 --> 00:15:20.790
So whatever happens. it's all on me.

211
00:15:21.030 --> 00:15:23.289
If you're going to be the bad guy no matter the result.

212
00:15:23.290 --> 00:15:24.800
you should at least win.

213
00:15:39.579 --> 00:15:40.680
You did this. didn't you?

214
00:15:45.719 --> 00:15:47.250
What exactly is my relationship with her?

215
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:54.089
You're not going to tell me?

216
00:15:57.559 --> 00:15:58.929
If you don't want to tell me. then don't.

217
00:15:58.930 --> 00:16:00.760
I'll figure it out myself.

218
00:16:02.030 --> 00:16:04.170
I didn't think you'd tell me anyway.

219
00:16:05.699 --> 00:16:09.140
Instead. don't resent me even if something happens.

220
00:16:35.800 --> 00:16:38.069
You kept going on about ghosts.

221
00:16:38.469 --> 00:16:40.839
and now you're even watching ghost dramas?

222
00:16:42.770 --> 00:16:43.968
What? What did you say?

223
00:16:43.969 --> 00:16:46.338
You're awfully energetic for someone who's fasting.

224
00:16:46.339 --> 00:16:49.279
Why are you starting the day watching such a scary drama?

225
00:16:49.280 --> 00:16:51.849
Aunt. I'm not watching this for fun.

226
00:16:51.979 --> 00:16:53.520
I'm studying right now.

227
00:16:54.589 --> 00:16:58.260
I need to study ghosts in order to... Wait a minute.

228
00:16:58.620 --> 00:17:01.089
What? Why does this situation feel so familiar?

229
00:17:01.859 --> 00:17:04.390
- My goodness. - Is it a deja vu?

230
00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:13.339
What? What are you doing here?

231
00:17:13.469 --> 00:17:15.938
Hey. watch it. Why are you talking that way to your doctor?

232
00:17:15.939 --> 00:17:18.040
"Doctor"? Who? Him?

233
00:17:19.109 --> 00:17:21.579
I'm sorry. She's still half-asleep.

234
00:17:22.109 --> 00:17:23.180
It's okay.

235
00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:25.549
She's not very healthy right now.

236
00:17:25.550 --> 00:17:28.318
So that could cause her to become hysterical and rude.

237
00:17:28.319 --> 00:17:29.848
What? "Rude"?

238
00:17:29.849 --> 00:17:31.160
Let me check your condition.

239
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:35.229
Hey. wait. Wait.

240
00:17:35.630 --> 00:17:36.829
Everything seems fine.

241
00:17:37.800 --> 00:17:39.559
Oh. gosh. Wait a minute.

242
00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:41.670
And that's fine too.

243
00:17:41.969 --> 00:17:44.400
Goodness. thank you. sir.

244
00:17:44.569 --> 00:17:46.938
Aunt. am I the only one who finds this weird? Really?

245
00:17:46.939 --> 00:17:47.939
Am I being strange right now?

246
00:17:47.939 --> 00:17:48.939
Yes. you're acting strange.

247
00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:51.439
We just need to take a few basic tests.

248
00:17:52.939 --> 00:17:53.979
Bye then.

249
00:17:57.150 --> 00:17:58.280
Unbelievable.

250
00:17:59.750 --> 00:18:00.979
What's with you?

251
00:18:02.489 --> 00:18:03.589
But he...

252
00:18:09.289 --> 00:18:10.330
You again?

253
00:18:11.199 --> 00:18:12.899
Stop chatting and sit.

254
00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:16.229
I can't believe this. Why do you keep following me around?

255
00:18:18.570 --> 00:18:21.469
- Hey. - Stay still. Don't move.

256
00:18:24.070 --> 00:18:26.478
Do you even know how to work this thing?

257
00:18:26.479 --> 00:18:27.640
Stop talking.

258
00:18:32.920 --> 00:18:34.849
Seriously. why are you doing this...

259
00:18:34.850 --> 00:18:35.989
Hold your breath.

260
00:18:39.820 --> 00:18:40.860
Good girl.

261
00:18:56.170 --> 00:18:58.739
How many jobs do you have?

262
00:18:58.880 --> 00:19:00.339
Why are you doing this to me?

263
00:19:00.340 --> 00:19:01.679
I'm here to save your life.

264
00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:03.009
What are you talking about?

265
00:19:06.779 --> 00:19:07.820
My gosh.

266
00:19:11.219 --> 00:19:13.219
If you go in there with this. you'll die.

267
00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:15.288
Do you know how expensive it is to fix this thing?

268
00:19:15.289 --> 00:19:16.430
I saved your life.

269
00:19:16.689 --> 00:19:18.798
So you're worried about the machine. not me?

270
00:19:18.799 --> 00:19:20.198
- Lie down. - Hey.

271
00:19:20.199 --> 00:19:21.299
Stop talking.

272
00:19:22.370 --> 00:19:25.269
Why does he keep telling me to stop talking?

273
00:20:12.249 --> 00:20:13.379
Hey. The more I think about it.

274
00:20:13.380 --> 00:20:15.948
I really don't know why I need to take this from you...

275
00:20:15.949 --> 00:20:17.188
Oh my gosh.

276
00:20:17.189 --> 00:20:20.089
Hey. Stop right there. I'm talking to you.

277
00:20:20.090 --> 00:20:21.958
- Hey! - Tak Dong Kyung?

278
00:20:21.959 --> 00:20:23.830
- Yes? - Let's go take your blood sample.

279
00:20:25.860 --> 00:20:27.299
Okay.

280
00:20:28.100 --> 00:20:29.170
Darn it.

281
00:20:29.499 --> 00:20:30.729
Ms. Tak!

282
00:20:31.340 --> 00:20:33.038
(Get well soon.)

283
00:20:33.039 --> 00:20:35.708
You need to bring fruit to someone in a hospital.

284
00:20:35.709 --> 00:20:37.110
so I picked out this and that.

285
00:20:38.110 --> 00:20:39.938
Can you even eat?

286
00:20:39.939 --> 00:20:42.080
- My fasting just ended. - What good timing.

287
00:20:42.509 --> 00:20:44.110
Is the hospital starving you?

288
00:20:44.580 --> 00:20:46.248
You need to eat well when you're sick.

289
00:20:46.249 --> 00:20:47.649
Eat. Eat everything.

290
00:20:47.650 --> 00:20:49.089
Say the word. I'll get it for you.

291
00:20:49.090 --> 00:20:50.449
I'm on standby 24 hours a day.

292
00:20:52.259 --> 00:20:54.860
I'll send you the pictures of hot guys that I collected.

293
00:20:55.729 --> 00:20:58.028
You must be bored here.

294
00:20:58.029 --> 00:20:59.298
I ask because I don't know.

295
00:20:59.299 --> 00:21:01.830
Does it make you less bored if you look at hot guys?

296
00:21:02.130 --> 00:21:03.999
Yes. it makes life enjoyable.

297
00:21:05.039 --> 00:21:06.539
They've gotten close.

298
00:21:06.699 --> 00:21:07.839
I know. right?

299
00:21:07.840 --> 00:21:10.268
I'm so proud. So proud.

300
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:11.810
- We're not close. - We're not close.

301
00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:15.709
Didn't you bring anything?

302
00:21:15.979 --> 00:21:17.649
You're the building owner's son.

303
00:21:17.650 --> 00:21:19.518
What? Come on.

304
00:21:19.519 --> 00:21:21.719
I'm sure he prepared at least a line.

305
00:21:22.549 --> 00:21:24.120
How have you been?

306
00:21:28.630 --> 00:21:29.729
Not that.

307
00:21:31.499 --> 00:21:34.458
Well... Tell me if you need cash.

308
00:21:34.459 --> 00:21:35.829
- Awesome. - Awesome.

309
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:36.900
He's so cool.

310
00:21:38.739 --> 00:21:40.439
How is that cool?

311
00:21:40.840 --> 00:21:42.340
Anyways. do you want to try this?

312
00:21:50.850 --> 00:21:52.718
Let's have some fruit.

313
00:21:52.719 --> 00:21:54.789
- Don't open it yet. - Eat with me.

314
00:21:55.219 --> 00:21:57.048
You eat it all. They're expensive.

315
00:21:57.049 --> 00:21:58.060
They are?

316
00:22:00.219 --> 00:22:02.059
I need to go. Something urgent came up.

317
00:22:02.060 --> 00:22:04.390
- What? So suddenly? - Sorry. I'll call you.

318
00:22:14.570 --> 00:22:16.170
I'm going drinking with Hyun Kyu.

319
00:22:18.310 --> 00:22:19.380
Go ahead.

320
00:22:20.539 --> 00:22:22.749
Shouldn't you stop me? You say you like me.

321
00:22:23.279 --> 00:22:24.748
What if I do something bad?

322
00:22:24.749 --> 00:22:25.779
Like what?

323
00:22:27.880 --> 00:22:28.948
Do it.

324
00:22:28.949 --> 00:22:30.590
It won't change my feelings.

325
00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:33.789
I wouldn't have told you how I felt if it were that flippant.

326
00:22:37.029 --> 00:22:38.400
Do you really like me?

327
00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:41.430
- Since when? - Since the beginning.

328
00:22:41.900 --> 00:22:43.229
When was that?

329
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:46.900
Since the beginning.

330
00:22:52.680 --> 00:22:53.779
You're insane.

331
00:22:55.709 --> 00:22:58.479
How could someone like you make such a stupid decision?

332
00:22:59.150 --> 00:23:00.150
I know.

333
00:23:02.650 --> 00:23:04.320
But losing what I want is what's truly stupid.

334
00:23:06.719 --> 00:23:09.360
Losing what you want is stupid. Ms. Na.

335
00:23:12.299 --> 00:23:13.560
Don't call me stupid.

336
00:23:14.299 --> 00:23:15.930
I thought about it for a long time.

337
00:23:16.799 --> 00:23:19.400
Why did I kiss someone I don't know?

338
00:23:20.100 --> 00:23:22.269
Why did it bother me so much...

339
00:23:22.640 --> 00:23:24.110
to see someone I don't know cry?

340
00:23:27.539 --> 00:23:29.080
The answer was there from the beginning.

341
00:23:30.479 --> 00:23:32.380
I told myself it was wrong. that's all.

342
00:23:38.160 --> 00:23:40.489
Does Hyun Kyu know too?

343
00:23:40.820 --> 00:23:41.890
What?

344
00:23:43.259 --> 00:23:44.529
That we kissed?

345
00:23:45.799 --> 00:23:46.830
Or...

346
00:23:48.870 --> 00:23:50.400
that I like you?

347
00:23:54.499 --> 00:23:57.310
He knows everything. He knew everything.

348
00:23:59.580 --> 00:24:01.180
That's why I can't back down.

349
00:24:03.910 --> 00:24:05.820
What do you think?

350
00:24:06.680 --> 00:24:08.189
Can I win?

351
00:24:09.219 --> 00:24:10.219
I don't know.

352
00:24:11.219 --> 00:24:12.860
Why don't you know anything?

353
00:24:15.729 --> 00:24:18.330
- Like you know? - I do.

354
00:24:32.239 --> 00:24:33.410
Spill it.

355
00:24:37.150 --> 00:24:38.820
I don't know. I'm going crazy.

356
00:24:40.219 --> 00:24:42.320
How did I become the bad girl?

357
00:24:42.850 --> 00:24:44.689
You're no bad girl.

358
00:24:45.019 --> 00:24:46.390
You're finally being rewarded.

359
00:24:46.719 --> 00:24:48.659
- I'm being rewarded? - No. it's an award.

360
00:24:48.660 --> 00:24:50.458
Mr. Cha is an award.

361
00:24:50.459 --> 00:24:51.459
Whatever.

362
00:24:51.460 --> 00:24:53.100
You always complained about him.

363
00:24:53.400 --> 00:24:54.998
I always thought...

364
00:24:54.999 --> 00:24:57.070
that jerk was a real pain.

365
00:24:57.729 --> 00:24:59.199
but he isn't a bad person.

366
00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:03.170
He doesn't give his heart that easily.

367
00:25:03.469 --> 00:25:05.339
That's why he still hasn't opened his heart to me.

368
00:25:05.340 --> 00:25:06.539
That annoying jerk.

369
00:25:09.150 --> 00:25:12.679
It's the end of Ji Na's tearjerker love stories.

370
00:25:12.680 --> 00:25:14.519
Finally. you met a good guy.

371
00:25:15.120 --> 00:25:17.119
That's right. You don't know. do you?

372
00:25:17.120 --> 00:25:18.120
What?

373
00:25:18.759 --> 00:25:19.890
He's...

374
00:25:21.630 --> 00:25:23.590
- mad loaded. - Really?

375
00:25:24.390 --> 00:25:26.059
No. no. It doesn't matter.

376
00:25:26.060 --> 00:25:27.559
Why doesn't it matter?

377
00:25:27.560 --> 00:25:29.600
To be honest. he's pretty good-looking.

378
00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:31.670
And this is a secret.

379
00:25:32.239 --> 00:25:34.640
I never said it in case he'd think I like him.

380
00:25:34.900 --> 00:25:36.009
To be honest.

381
00:25:37.469 --> 00:25:39.910
he's really funny at times.

382
00:25:40.610 --> 00:25:41.708
He really is funny.

383
00:25:41.709 --> 00:25:43.549
I bet he'll make you laugh every day if you go out with him.

384
00:25:47.150 --> 00:25:49.149
I don't know. Should I see a fortune-teller?

385
00:25:49.150 --> 00:25:50.620
A fortune-teller? Should we go together?

386
00:25:51.019 --> 00:25:53.320
- You too? Why? - Some freak...

387
00:25:53.519 --> 00:25:54.688
No. a doctor...

388
00:25:54.689 --> 00:25:57.129
No. no. I don't know how to describe this.

389
00:25:57.130 --> 00:25:58.429
What is it? Is a doctor hitting on you?

390
00:25:58.430 --> 00:26:00.729
Yes. He keeps saying let's end the world together.

391
00:26:01.029 --> 00:26:02.329
Oh my gosh. He says...

392
00:26:02.330 --> 00:26:04.130
he'll love only you even if the world ends?

393
00:26:04.370 --> 00:26:05.999
When did I say that?

394
00:26:06.370 --> 00:26:08.439
- That's not it... - Awesome.

395
00:26:09.070 --> 00:26:11.208
A hot doctor falls for a patient at first sight...

396
00:26:11.209 --> 00:26:12.739
and begs for her love.

397
00:26:13.479 --> 00:26:15.179
What an amazing hospital romance.

398
00:26:15.180 --> 00:26:16.449
It is not!

399
00:26:17.209 --> 00:26:18.249
Hey.

400
00:26:19.120 --> 00:26:21.080
Forget it. Just forget it.

401
00:26:25.110 --> 00:26:26.411
- Sir. - Yes?

402
00:26:27.350 --> 00:26:28.981
Why did you open a cafe?

403
00:26:30.780 --> 00:26:32.251
You were a swimmer.

404
00:26:32.691 --> 00:26:33.850
You even studied abroad.

405
00:26:34.520 --> 00:26:35.721
Why do you ask?

406
00:26:38.731 --> 00:26:40.761
I sincerely like working at a cafe.

407
00:26:41.830 --> 00:26:44.300
You look like you were born to own a cafe.

408
00:26:45.370 --> 00:26:46.770
But I'm not sure about myself.

409
00:26:48.201 --> 00:26:49.270
Well...

410
00:26:49.971 --> 00:26:52.039
After I got injured while studying abroad.

411
00:26:52.040 --> 00:26:53.741
I was completely lost.

412
00:26:54.241 --> 00:26:56.011
I suddenly missed Korea like crazy.

413
00:26:56.741 --> 00:26:59.350
So I stopped by a cafe...

414
00:27:00.651 --> 00:27:02.280
and that was when I realized...

415
00:27:02.751 --> 00:27:04.850
that coffee was the same there or in Korea.

416
00:27:06.820 --> 00:27:08.491
Is that how you fell in love with coffee?

417
00:27:08.961 --> 00:27:10.060
No. that's a lie.

418
00:27:10.860 --> 00:27:14.360
It looks cool to own a cafe.

419
00:27:15.800 --> 00:27:17.859
Don't wait for destiny.

420
00:27:17.860 --> 00:27:20.401
It won't hit you on the head saying it's fate.

421
00:27:20.870 --> 00:27:23.171
I never knew I'd run a cafe either.

422
00:27:24.671 --> 00:27:25.941
If you like it. do it.

423
00:27:26.241 --> 00:27:28.441
Don't make plans and make a big deal out of it.

424
00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:30.211
Just do it.

425
00:27:30.641 --> 00:27:32.810
You'll become good at it eventually.

426
00:27:33.481 --> 00:27:36.050
Then you'll think you were meant for it.

427
00:27:39.391 --> 00:27:41.691
You're good. You're doing well.

428
00:27:47.961 --> 00:27:50.431
Don't you think it was a waste?

429
00:27:51.300 --> 00:27:52.931
What can I do though?

430
00:27:53.130 --> 00:27:55.000
I wasn't good enough to make the national team.

431
00:27:55.001 --> 00:27:57.671
Not that. Your first love.

432
00:28:00.570 --> 00:28:02.879
If you knew you were meant to run a cafe.

433
00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:04.241
you wouldn't have left to study abroad.

434
00:28:04.741 --> 00:28:07.050
Then you may have stayed together.

435
00:28:08.951 --> 00:28:10.780
And you wouldn't be hurt like this.

436
00:28:12.191 --> 00:28:13.491
She's the one...

437
00:28:15.360 --> 00:28:16.921
who was hurt. not I.

438
00:28:17.820 --> 00:28:18.931
I just...

439
00:28:21.261 --> 00:28:23.100
I just kept running away.

440
00:28:28.840 --> 00:28:30.070
It's okay.

441
00:28:30.840 --> 00:28:32.370
Just don't run away anymore.

442
00:28:33.011 --> 00:28:34.671
What? Do I look like a fool to you?

443
00:28:36.141 --> 00:28:37.211
A bit.

444
00:28:37.840 --> 00:28:38.850
You punk.

445
00:28:39.610 --> 00:28:41.151
My gosh. Who put away the beans like that?

446
00:28:41.580 --> 00:28:44.550
It was me. Gosh. I'm so stupid. I'm such a fool!

447
00:29:01.231 --> 00:29:06.641
(Ji Na)

448
00:29:14.911 --> 00:29:15.921
Hello?

449
00:29:16.981 --> 00:29:18.350
Drink with me tonight.

450
00:29:31.600 --> 00:29:33.330
Sure. Let's do that.

451
00:29:35.600 --> 00:29:38.201
Mr. Lee. what do I do with the expired beans...

452
00:29:42.481 --> 00:29:43.810
Let me go and get changed.

453
00:29:51.751 --> 00:29:53.421
You were working at this cafe?

454
00:29:53.991 --> 00:29:57.191
Yes. This is the cafe. But why are you...

455
00:29:58.830 --> 00:30:00.431
Athlete. swimmer. and running away...

456
00:30:05.330 --> 00:30:06.529
I sort of figured it out.

457
00:30:06.530 --> 00:30:08.400
But let me ask just one question to confirm it.

458
00:30:08.401 --> 00:30:09.441
What?

459
00:30:09.901 --> 00:30:12.010
Is my boss number 1 or 2?

460
00:30:12.011 --> 00:30:13.070
What?

461
00:30:13.711 --> 00:30:17.280
You told me you wanted to kill two guys. Which one is he?

462
00:30:20.350 --> 00:30:22.280
- Number one. - Gosh. Mr. Lee.

463
00:30:23.151 --> 00:30:24.951
Lock up for me. Thanks.

464
00:30:25.451 --> 00:30:26.491
- Let's go. - Okay.

465
00:30:27.290 --> 00:30:28.290
- I... - Shut it.

466
00:30:30.560 --> 00:30:31.620
Bye.

467
00:30:47.011 --> 00:30:48.610
Slow down.

468
00:30:48.911 --> 00:30:50.441
You might do something you'll regret.

469
00:30:55.681 --> 00:30:58.421
Sure. Do whatever you want. I'll forget about it.

470
00:31:04.461 --> 00:31:05.991
I guess that's easy for you.

471
00:31:07.991 --> 00:31:12.300
You said you came back to Korea and attended the reunion to see me.

472
00:31:13.800 --> 00:31:14.900
Yes.

473
00:31:14.901 --> 00:31:15.971
Same here.

474
00:31:16.340 --> 00:31:18.610
I went to the reunion to see you every year.

475
00:31:21.241 --> 00:31:23.981
- Let's drink. Drink up. - Okay.

476
00:31:25.850 --> 00:31:27.280
"What if he doesn't come?"

477
00:31:28.751 --> 00:31:31.451
"But what if he really came?" That's all I thought about.

478
00:31:33.251 --> 00:31:34.420
I was disappointed every time.

479
00:31:34.421 --> 00:31:36.590
anticipating seeing you as I sat there.

480
00:31:39.290 --> 00:31:40.530
That's not all.

481
00:31:42.300 --> 00:31:43.930
I couldn't go to your house.

482
00:31:43.931 --> 00:31:46.100
So I roamed around your neighborhood.

483
00:31:48.001 --> 00:31:50.201
I sat at a cafe near your house too.

484
00:31:51.070 --> 00:31:53.640
(Danger. No Entry)

485
00:31:53.641 --> 00:31:55.410
I used to get off at a subway station...

486
00:31:55.411 --> 00:31:56.941
near your house and sit on the bench.

487
00:32:03.550 --> 00:32:06.619
Whenever the doors opened. just in case you got off.

488
00:32:06.620 --> 00:32:09.360
I was nervous and tense.

489
00:32:11.290 --> 00:32:13.260
In case I ran into you by chance.

490
00:32:13.261 --> 00:32:14.891
I kept roaming around your streets.

491
00:32:17.431 --> 00:32:20.100
- I didn't know. - I don't resent you.

492
00:32:20.931 --> 00:32:22.540
Don't look so guilty.

493
00:32:24.001 --> 00:32:25.711
I just wanted to tell you...

494
00:32:26.610 --> 00:32:29.280
that I had been loving you for a very long time by myself.

495
00:32:32.181 --> 00:32:33.951
In my head.

496
00:32:34.481 --> 00:32:36.721
I had always loved you by myself.

497
00:32:39.451 --> 00:32:40.520
But...

498
00:32:42.620 --> 00:32:45.020
seeing you again lately made me wonder...

499
00:32:46.261 --> 00:32:47.830
if the person I loved...

500
00:32:49.661 --> 00:32:51.401
was truly you.

501
00:32:52.530 --> 00:32:53.671
What do you mean?

502
00:32:54.330 --> 00:32:56.870
I don't know anything about you.

503
00:32:57.901 --> 00:32:59.540
I realized it when I started to see you again.

504
00:33:00.610 --> 00:33:02.280
I had been in love with...

505
00:33:03.941 --> 00:33:05.310
the 18-year-old you.

506
00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:10.751
I had been waiting for you on the same spot...

507
00:33:12.951 --> 00:33:14.891
when you had walked away.

508
00:33:15.820 --> 00:33:17.461
It's the same with me.

509
00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:21.830
I don't know anything about you either.

510
00:33:22.800 --> 00:33:25.300
- Yes. That's why... - But I don't care.

511
00:33:26.300 --> 00:33:27.530
I won't run away now.

512
00:33:28.330 --> 00:33:30.701
- Our relationship ended long ago. - It ended?

513
00:33:32.641 --> 00:33:34.610
I had been a swimmer for over 10 years.

514
00:33:35.011 --> 00:33:38.280
Going back to the starting line isn't that hard for me.

515
00:33:38.880 --> 00:33:40.550
I can go back over and over again.

516
00:33:50.491 --> 00:33:52.089
Cha Joo Ik and I kissed.

517
00:33:52.090 --> 00:33:53.491
I know. I don't care.

518
00:33:53.931 --> 00:33:55.261
I care.

519
00:34:03.600 --> 00:34:04.671
I think...

520
00:34:06.241 --> 00:34:07.911
it matters to me.

521
00:34:17.780 --> 00:34:18.820
Na Ji Na.

522
00:34:21.690 --> 00:34:22.960
You're horrible.

523
00:34:37.241 --> 00:34:38.241
You're crying again.

524
00:34:39.771 --> 00:34:40.840
Why...

525
00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:43.541
are you here?

526
00:34:44.041 --> 00:34:45.141
I don't know.

527
00:34:46.150 --> 00:34:48.280
How long have you been waiting here?

528
00:34:49.050 --> 00:34:50.181
I don't know.

529
00:34:52.121 --> 00:34:54.190
What if I didn't show up?

530
00:34:54.951 --> 00:34:56.190
I don't know that either.

531
00:34:59.590 --> 00:35:00.630
Seriously.

532
00:35:01.761 --> 00:35:02.930
You're ridiculous.

533
00:35:02.931 --> 00:35:04.360
I get that a lot.

534
00:35:04.931 --> 00:35:07.471
You never disappoint me with your unexpected behaviors.

535
00:35:09.271 --> 00:35:10.541
You confuse me.

536
00:35:10.701 --> 00:35:11.940
I confuse you?

537
00:35:13.911 --> 00:35:15.511
I don't think so.

538
00:35:24.280 --> 00:35:25.420
Don't be confused.

539
00:35:26.991 --> 00:35:30.161
I came here because I wanted to see you and I like you.

540
00:36:03.820 --> 00:36:04.891
What was that?

541
00:36:05.690 --> 00:36:07.630
I didn't want to drink because if I did.

542
00:36:10.101 --> 00:36:12.170
I might do something that I would regret.

543
00:36:18.300 --> 00:36:19.411
Ms. Na.

544
00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:22.480
Ms. Na.

545
00:37:24.771 --> 00:37:26.940
Limit your regrets only to me.

546
00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:29.940
Your regrettable action...

547
00:37:30.541 --> 00:37:32.181
could destroy me.

548
00:38:05.011 --> 00:38:06.780
You crazy wench. Na Ji Na!

549
00:38:08.210 --> 00:38:09.820
Gosh. Come on.

550
00:38:12.750 --> 00:38:16.021
- What? My hair? - Yes.

551
00:38:16.661 --> 00:38:19.260
You'll be going through chemo and radiation therapy.

552
00:38:19.261 --> 00:38:20.460
Your hair will fall out quickly.

553
00:38:21.431 --> 00:38:22.761
You've seen it on TV. right?

554
00:38:23.201 --> 00:38:24.629
You might cope better...

555
00:38:24.630 --> 00:38:26.201
if you take care of your hair beforehand.

556
00:38:27.070 --> 00:38:28.500
And that's what I recommend too.

557
00:38:30.041 --> 00:38:32.241
Seeing your hair falling out...

558
00:38:33.871 --> 00:38:35.440
could be harder to watch.

559
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:51.090
Ever since you were young. you had a nice shaped head.

560
00:38:51.891 --> 00:38:53.930
So whenever I gave you a short haircut.

561
00:38:53.931 --> 00:38:56.161
all the elders in the neighborhood...

562
00:38:56.661 --> 00:39:00.371
would say you look like a cute chestnut...

563
00:39:01.070 --> 00:39:02.670
and give you tons of compliments.

564
00:39:03.371 --> 00:39:04.541
You remember that. right?

565
00:39:05.241 --> 00:39:07.041
Yes. I remember.

566
00:39:07.440 --> 00:39:08.610
Your hair...

567
00:39:11.011 --> 00:39:12.351
will grow.

568
00:39:13.811 --> 00:39:15.081
It'll grow back really fast.

569
00:39:15.581 --> 00:39:17.550
They also sell shampoos that help your hair grow faster.

570
00:39:19.221 --> 00:39:20.249
Right.

571
00:39:20.250 --> 00:39:22.121
Should I also get a haircut?

572
00:39:23.021 --> 00:39:25.991
We can make Sun Kyung shave his head too.

573
00:39:28.791 --> 00:39:31.629
Don't you remember he did that when he went to the army?

574
00:39:31.630 --> 00:39:33.331
He was really ugly.

575
00:39:34.471 --> 00:39:36.041
He looks decent thanks to his hair. so he can't shave his head.

576
00:39:36.900 --> 00:39:40.910
Shaving my head is already enough. Let's not do it to anyone else.

577
00:39:40.911 --> 00:39:41.940
Okay. Auntie?

578
00:39:44.110 --> 00:39:47.081
Gosh. you charming girl. You're such a good girl.

579
00:39:48.210 --> 00:39:52.621
I should go and buy you some hats.

580
00:39:54.021 --> 00:39:55.649
I'll get you pretty ones.

581
00:39:55.650 --> 00:39:58.390
Don't bother. I have a lot of hats.

582
00:39:58.391 --> 00:40:00.060
You even bought me one last time.

583
00:40:00.061 --> 00:40:01.830
Gosh. that's too big.

584
00:40:01.831 --> 00:40:03.530
You have a tiny head.

585
00:40:04.261 --> 00:40:05.971
Let me take a look.

586
00:40:09.541 --> 00:40:10.601
It's about this big.

587
00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:13.210
I'll be right back.

588
00:41:45.630 --> 00:41:47.800
(Absolute rest)

589
00:41:57.811 --> 00:41:59.911
How should I style your hair?

590
00:42:01.911 --> 00:42:03.820
Well...

591
00:42:06.721 --> 00:42:08.121
I want to look like a celebrity.

592
00:42:08.491 --> 00:42:10.060
- Pardon? - Something that celebrities do.

593
00:42:10.061 --> 00:42:13.830
I want a perm that looks really extravagant.

594
00:42:13.831 --> 00:42:14.860
Just like that.

595
00:42:16.130 --> 00:42:17.161
Miss.

596
00:42:18.460 --> 00:42:20.030
That was done with a curling iron.

597
00:42:22.101 --> 00:42:23.170
I want that hairstyle.

598
00:42:27.511 --> 00:42:29.380
There. You're all done.

599
00:42:31.780 --> 00:42:35.311
To be honest. I was a little worried because you came in a patient gown.

600
00:42:36.121 --> 00:42:38.621
We get a few patients from the hospital nearby.

601
00:42:38.951 --> 00:42:40.420
and they come to shave their heads.

602
00:42:42.920 --> 00:42:44.690
This hair looks great on you.

603
00:42:45.491 --> 00:42:48.561
Can we take a photo and upload it on our website?

604
00:42:49.061 --> 00:42:51.101
Your face won't show. It'll just be your hair.

605
00:42:51.561 --> 00:42:53.630
- Just your hair. - Okay.

606
00:42:54.601 --> 00:42:56.840
The curls came out great.

607
00:43:02.880 --> 00:43:05.180
- Are you done? - Wait. Just one more.

608
00:43:05.181 --> 00:43:06.181
I'll take it from here.

609
00:43:08.451 --> 00:43:09.521
It looks so pretty.

610
00:43:10.420 --> 00:43:11.780
You're all done now.

611
00:43:12.621 --> 00:43:13.650
Okay then.

612
00:43:14.650 --> 00:43:16.061
You can shave my head now.

613
00:43:17.521 --> 00:43:18.561
What?

614
00:43:21.261 --> 00:43:23.561
Just shave everything off my head.

615
00:43:25.971 --> 00:43:29.170
I'm sorry. I know you put in a lot of effort to do this for me.

616
00:43:30.101 --> 00:43:32.610
But I wanted to try it one last time.

617
00:43:34.141 --> 00:43:36.380
It won't be your last time. You should come again.

618
00:43:37.110 --> 00:43:38.310
I'll do this for you again.

619
00:43:38.311 --> 00:43:40.050
I'll make sure it comes out even better than today.

620
00:43:40.911 --> 00:43:44.780
Actually. I bet you'll look good with short hair too.

621
00:43:46.221 --> 00:43:48.319
Now that I think of it. it wasn't the hair that came out nice.

622
00:43:48.320 --> 00:43:50.460
You're just pretty to begin with.

623
00:43:53.561 --> 00:43:55.030
Will you be okay?

624
00:43:58.900 --> 00:43:59.900
Yes.

625
00:44:10.780 --> 00:44:11.980
I'll cut it now.

626
00:44:14.710 --> 00:44:15.750
Okay.

627
00:44:18.181 --> 00:44:19.891
- Your nose is bleeding. - My goodness.

628
00:44:20.351 --> 00:44:22.350
- Are you okay? - Oh. yes. I'm sorry.

629
00:44:22.351 --> 00:44:23.490
- Get her a tissue. - I'm fine.

630
00:44:23.491 --> 00:44:25.291
Just a second. Get her a tissue.

631
00:46:06.230 --> 00:46:07.560
Don't cry.

632
00:46:12.270 --> 00:46:13.739
Don't cry.

633
00:46:43.270 --> 00:46:44.469
Don't cry.

634
00:46:46.870 --> 00:46:48.799
Please don't cry.

635
00:47:35.580 --> 00:47:36.819
I'm sorry.

636
00:47:38.889 --> 00:47:40.389
I'm so sorry.

637
00:49:18.319 --> 00:49:19.319
What's going on?

638
00:49:19.960 --> 00:49:21.659
Where am I?

639
00:49:22.420 --> 00:49:23.488
My house.

640
00:49:23.489 --> 00:49:25.489
Why am I in your house?

641
00:49:27.830 --> 00:49:29.559
Was I kidnapped?

642
00:49:29.560 --> 00:49:30.630
Something like that.

643
00:49:31.130 --> 00:49:33.670
Since I dragged you into this dream without your consent.

644
00:49:34.799 --> 00:49:35.870
Dream?

645
00:49:45.350 --> 00:49:46.580
This is a dream?

646
00:49:50.750 --> 00:49:52.489
What... Wow.

647
00:49:53.859 --> 00:49:55.489
It feels so real.

648
00:49:56.060 --> 00:49:57.060
That's right.

649
00:50:05.429 --> 00:50:06.429
What?

650
00:50:17.480 --> 00:50:19.179
(Les Miserables)

651
00:50:23.350 --> 00:50:24.650
You're giving me a headache.

652
00:50:30.989 --> 00:50:32.230
Is this jail?

653
00:50:32.659 --> 00:50:34.529
Did you lock me up?

654
00:50:35.359 --> 00:50:37.529
Is that all you can say to the person who saved your life?

655
00:50:38.370 --> 00:50:39.429
What?

656
00:50:40.370 --> 00:50:41.500
You saved me?

657
00:50:42.440 --> 00:50:43.670
Wasn't that a dream?

658
00:50:44.040 --> 00:50:45.810
No. it wasn't.

659
00:50:47.710 --> 00:50:50.480
Then that dream... No.

660
00:50:50.880 --> 00:50:53.278
That was a dream. It was definitely a dream.

661
00:50:53.279 --> 00:50:55.679
It was a dream. So why...

662
00:50:56.350 --> 00:50:57.389
That dream?

663
00:50:57.650 --> 00:51:01.219
You were crying in my dream earlier.

664
00:51:01.889 --> 00:51:02.960
It was a dream.

665
00:51:03.690 --> 00:51:05.929
I don't eat. sleep. or cry.

666
00:51:06.489 --> 00:51:09.900
I died and you came to my funeral.

667
00:51:10.799 --> 00:51:14.600
You looked at my picture and cried...

668
00:51:28.350 --> 00:51:29.549
I'm not sad.

669
00:51:35.259 --> 00:51:36.889
I'm not sad no matter how much I look at you.

670
00:51:37.859 --> 00:51:40.630
Hey. You startled me.

671
00:51:42.029 --> 00:51:43.999
- Smile. - What?

672
00:51:44.000 --> 00:51:45.629
Smile at me.

673
00:51:45.630 --> 00:51:46.698
Why should I?

674
00:51:46.699 --> 00:51:48.900
I need to know who and what you are.

675
00:51:49.600 --> 00:51:51.310
Will you know if I smile?

676
00:52:01.779 --> 00:52:02.920
Smile again.

677
00:52:14.460 --> 00:52:15.500
I have no idea.

678
00:52:17.799 --> 00:52:19.469
Where are you going?

679
00:52:20.339 --> 00:52:22.399
Where are you going?

680
00:52:22.400 --> 00:52:23.469
Outside.

681
00:52:23.770 --> 00:52:26.210
We need to go somewhere open. It's too dangerous here.

682
00:52:26.880 --> 00:52:29.949
Gosh. Why? Do you think I'll do something to you?

683
00:52:31.009 --> 00:52:34.179
No. I'm afraid I'll do something to you.

684
00:52:35.980 --> 00:52:37.019
Like what?

685
00:52:37.020 --> 00:52:40.120
Who knows? Since I don't know who you are.

686
00:52:41.089 --> 00:52:42.619
Run away if I do.

687
00:52:42.620 --> 00:52:44.130
Run as hard as you can.

688
00:52:45.790 --> 00:52:47.830
Are you sure it's safer outside?

689
00:52:52.569 --> 00:52:53.770
There's nothing dangerous...

690
00:52:55.569 --> 00:52:57.069
since nothing there is alive.

691
00:53:11.489 --> 00:53:14.690
- What is this place? - My subconscious.

692
00:53:15.520 --> 00:53:16.690
Subconscious?

693
00:53:17.089 --> 00:53:18.730
It's like your ocean.

694
00:53:39.109 --> 00:53:41.949
- That was why. - What?

695
00:53:42.219 --> 00:53:44.319
You say this is like my ocean.

696
00:53:45.319 --> 00:53:47.389
So this was how you felt.

697
00:53:48.020 --> 00:53:51.130
That was why you were so prickly.

698
00:53:51.529 --> 00:53:54.159
Don't talk gibberish. Just remember.

699
00:53:54.859 --> 00:53:56.968
Do you really not know me?

700
00:53:56.969 --> 00:53:58.270
No. I don't.

701
00:53:59.299 --> 00:54:01.068
Think before you speak.

702
00:54:01.069 --> 00:54:03.039
Why do I need to think about something like that?

703
00:54:03.040 --> 00:54:04.210
I just know.

704
00:54:09.639 --> 00:54:12.009
I don't need to think to know that you're pretty.

705
00:54:18.190 --> 00:54:19.190
Hey.

706
00:54:20.989 --> 00:54:21.989
Have you been here before?

707
00:54:21.990 --> 00:54:23.460
Obviously. not.

708
00:54:23.489 --> 00:54:25.359
You should think before you talk.

709
00:54:25.830 --> 00:54:28.460
Why? Do you remember seeing me here?

710
00:54:35.839 --> 00:54:37.770
You really must have seen me before.

711
00:54:38.670 --> 00:54:39.710
I have not.

712
00:54:41.210 --> 00:54:42.810
- Then why... - I don't know.

713
00:54:44.179 --> 00:54:48.020
Seriously. You need to learn how to speak again.

714
00:54:50.250 --> 00:54:53.659
You need to make sense. Talk in longer sentences.

715
00:54:54.020 --> 00:54:55.988
What's the use in reading books all the time?

716
00:54:55.989 --> 00:54:58.529
Hey. Be honest with me.

717
00:54:58.690 --> 00:55:01.500
You don't read. do you? You just hold them. don't you?

718
00:55:04.569 --> 00:55:06.230
There's a line that the author wrote.

719
00:55:07.000 --> 00:55:08.770
"Dying is nothing."

720
00:55:09.299 --> 00:55:12.370
"What is frightening is not living to the fullest."

721
00:55:14.040 --> 00:55:15.309
Are you saying that to me?

722
00:55:15.310 --> 00:55:17.210
No. To myself.

723
00:55:18.210 --> 00:55:19.650
Because I'm nothing.

724
00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:22.650
Because I'm not alive.

725
00:55:27.290 --> 00:55:30.230
There's another famous quote by that author.

726
00:55:31.429 --> 00:55:34.230
"The reduction of the universe to one person."

727
00:55:34.500 --> 00:55:36.659
"and the expansion of one person to a deity."

728
00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:38.799
"That is love."

729
00:55:43.069 --> 00:55:45.770
Remember beautiful things from now on.

730
00:55:46.339 --> 00:55:49.509
Then this place may become...

731
00:55:50.040 --> 00:55:51.679
a little nicer.

732
00:56:38.259 --> 00:56:39.359
Why...

733
00:56:41.730 --> 00:56:43.259
What is this...

734
00:56:51.569 --> 00:56:52.739
Will you choose to do that?

735
00:56:56.440 --> 00:56:57.850
There's not much time.

736
00:56:58.880 --> 00:57:00.350
You need to make a choice.

737
00:57:26.870 --> 00:57:28.040
I'll do it.

738
00:57:33.279 --> 00:57:34.420
I'll do it.

739
00:57:58.670 --> 00:58:00.540
(Ask the world to end before dying.)

740
00:58:01.580 --> 00:58:03.980
(Doom. person I love the most)

741
00:58:08.150 --> 00:58:10.650
(Doom. person I love the most)

742
00:59:46.710 --> 00:59:48.350
Oh. no.

743
01:00:51.980 --> 01:00:54.319
I must be going crazy.

744
01:00:55.819 --> 01:00:57.190
I must be really sick.

745
01:01:13.730 --> 01:01:15.699
(Ms. Soo Ja)

746
01:01:18.139 --> 01:01:20.579
- Auntie. - Where are you?

747
01:01:20.580 --> 01:01:22.509
I left something at my house.

748
01:01:22.980 --> 01:01:24.049
I'll be there soon.

749
01:01:24.750 --> 01:01:25.779
Okay.

750
01:01:38.929 --> 01:01:41.159
(Human)

751
01:01:57.040 --> 01:01:58.080
Hello?

752
01:02:36.980 --> 01:02:37.989
You...

753
01:02:39.989 --> 01:02:41.219
How could you...

754
01:02:44.230 --> 01:02:47.330
How could you forget about me?

755
01:02:47.830 --> 01:02:49.029
Right back at you.

756
01:02:49.600 --> 01:02:51.870
Even if I made that decision.

757
01:02:52.069 --> 01:02:53.969
you should have recognized me right away.

758
01:02:54.270 --> 01:02:56.799
You should have remembered me.

759
01:02:57.670 --> 01:02:58.770
That's my fault?

760
01:02:59.469 --> 01:03:01.080
Who told you to make that decision?

761
01:03:02.509 --> 01:03:05.678
You did whatever you wanted without talking to me.

762
01:03:05.679 --> 01:03:08.119
You know what? Even when you lost your memory.

763
01:03:08.120 --> 01:03:09.980
your nasty temper didn't go away.

764
01:03:10.420 --> 01:03:12.620
Did you find me handsome even when you lost your memory?

765
01:04:28.400 --> 01:04:32.299
(Doom at Your Service)

766
01:04:32.600 --> 01:04:34.239
We can't escape...

767
01:04:35.699 --> 01:04:37.339
our fate. right?

768
01:04:39.770 --> 01:04:42.239
So we should accept it now.

769
01:04:42.980 --> 01:04:44.880
Will it hurt a lot when I die?

770
01:04:45.409 --> 01:04:49.350
You knew that I would be making this decision. right?

771
01:04:50.219 --> 01:04:53.819
I don't know what I will decide.

772
01:04:55.219 --> 01:04:56.389
We should go.

773
01:04:57.120 --> 01:04:58.159
Bye.

774
01:04:59.259 --> 01:05:00.929
I didn't give up yet.

775
01:05:01.500 --> 01:05:03.799
- Help us. - Accept it.

776
01:05:04.969 --> 01:05:06.069
I love you.

777
01:05:06.500 --> 01:05:08.739
Thank you for loving me.
